{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Very soon after arriving there, I found out that a-- a letter had arrived from the Hebrew Union College in Cincinnati asking the seminary to send five of its students to Cincinnati to complete their studies there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Julian Morgenstern, the president of the Hebrew Union College, had a feeling for what was going to happen in Germany, even though only the beginnings of the persecutions and the exclusion of Jews had happened.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was farsighted enough to feel that this would make a difference.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And indeed it made a difference between life and death for-- I'm sure, for some of us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I applied for one of those five positions, and strangely, out of a student body of probably 150 or so, there were only about eight or nine who applied, of whom six were found to be eligible as far as the administration of the school was concerned.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So one day, the two youngest of those six were asked to come to the dean's office, and we were told that the remaining four applicants were definitely accepted, but since there were only five spaces, only one of the two of us, being the two youngest and the most recent arrivals at the seminary, would be able to go.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Just as the dean prepared a couple of pieces of paper so that we could draw and see who will draw the long and who would draw the short, the door opened, and one of the other four came in and said that his parents would not permit him to leave, which meant that both of us could go.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So that was in April-- no, in-- in May of 1935.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in September, the five of us started for the United States.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
